00:01:09.090 --> 00:01:17.031
M9A1
The first handgun to review is the M9A1 this

00:01:17.031 --> 00:01:22.860
feels like a very well rounded gun even though
its stats tell a different story, it has high

00:01:22.860 --> 00:01:28.130
damage and large clips for its class and is
a very accessable pistol for people not use

00:01:28.130 --> 00:01:34.550
to using handguns and is a pleasure to use.

00:01:34.550 --> 00:01:42.439
MP-444 Grach
The Grach is a solid and balanced pistol with

00:01:42.439 --> 00:01:48.509
low recoil and 15 rounds in a mag as standard
and has the highest fire rate in its class,

00:01:48.509 --> 00:01:54.479
the first 3 handguns are all very similar
weapons so which one suits you better is more

00:01:54.479 --> 00:02:00.450
a matter of preference than anything else
but for me this is the least satisfying gun

00:02:00.450 --> 00:02:06.200
as it's a little weak and feels cheap compared
to most other guns in this category and ends

00:02:06.200 --> 00:02:13.140
up feeling like a poor mans P226.

00:02:13.140 --> 00:02:21.790
P226
The P226 is a very balanced weapon with the

00:02:21.790 --> 00:02:27.540
largest magazine of all pistols and comes
with great damage, range and further more

00:02:27.540 --> 00:02:34.400
is very satisfying to use, on the downside
it has a fair amount of recoil but all pistols

00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:41.030
aside from one handgun has recoil that is
easily manageable so this isn't really that

00:02:41.030 --> 00:02:47.530
big of a deal.

00:02:47.530 --> 00:02:53.120
.44 Magnum
The magnum has the best range and by far the

00:02:53.120 --> 00:03:00.019
most power of any pistol and as it is a revolver
it has 6 rounds in a magazine.

00:03:00.019 --> 00:03:05.340
On the negative side it has the slowest fire
rate and mobility compared to all other weapons

00:03:05.340 --> 00:03:10.970
in this category, however those points are
kinda irrelevant as the thing that really

00:03:10.970 --> 00:03:16.580
holds this weapon back is the unmanageable
amount of recoil which makes it really hard

00:03:16.580 --> 00:03:22.420
to hit anything after firing the first shot,
that aside this gun is kinda meant to be a

00:03:22.420 --> 00:03:28.760
bit of a novelty and thus probably isn't a
secondary to rely on but is most definitely

00:03:28.760 --> 00:03:40.000
the go to choice if you want to have some
fun.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:45.650
PDW
The PDW is a 3 round burst fire handgun which

00:03:45.650 --> 00:03:51.720
comes with 18 rounds in a mag and supposedly
has a high fire rate and moderate recoil,

00:03:51.720 --> 00:03:58.050
making this weapon very similar in design
to the B23R from black ops 2, however that's

00:03:58.050 --> 00:04:04.360
where the similarity ends as this gun doesn't
really work as it's not all that powerful

00:04:04.360 --> 00:04:10.159
and the fire rate between each burst is really
slow also due to the fact that your firing

00:04:10.159 --> 00:04:16.260
3 rounds at a time the clip capacity is more
like 6 rounds in a magazine instead of 18

00:04:16.260 --> 00:04:22.400
and to top it off this gun isn't all that
fun to use, so in my opinion I'd steer clear

00:04:22.400 --> 00:04:38.010
unless this weapon gets buffed at a later
date.

00:04:38.010 --> 00:04:43.010
So that's my thoughts and analysis of the
handgun class so far, this category can be

00:04:43.010 --> 00:04:49.330
genuinely useful as a secondary weapon or
even as a primary in the right situations

00:04:49.330 --> 00:04:54.789
assuming you have set up your perks correctly
and have a tac knife, on the other hand you

00:04:54.789 --> 00:05:00.290
may wish to have no secondary and take an
extra perk instead, this decision is purely

00:05:00.290 --> 00:05:05.399
up to personal preference and you should set
up your load-out as to which of these strategies

00:05:05.399 --> 00:05:07.909
most suits your play style.

00:05:07.909 --> 00:05:13.080
